name: ClassChecker
desc: A utility class to check Dart classes for specific criteria related to Firestorm objects.

name: checkClassesForValidFSTypes
desc: Checks if the classes have valid types for Firestore.

name: checkClassesForValidRDBTypes
desc: Checks if the classes have valid RDB types.

name: filter
desc:
Filters the provided iterable of ClassElements to find valid classes for Firestorm.
Returns a ValidClassHolder containing two lists: one for Firestore valid classes and one for RDB valid classes.

name: findAnnotatedClasses
desc:
Finds all classes annotated with @FirestormObject in the provided iterable of ClassElements.
Returns a list of ClassElements that are annotated with @FirestormObject.

name: findClassesWithIDField
desc:
Finds all classes that have an ID field of type String from a list of classes.
Checks both the class itself and its superclasses for an ID field.
Returns a list of ClassElements that meet the criteria.

name: findClassesWithPublicNoArgConstructor
desc:
Finds all classes that have a public, no-argument constructor from a list of classes.
Returns a list of ClassElements that meet the criteria.

name: isEnumType
desc: Checks if the given DartType is an enum.

name: RegistryGenerator
desc: Generates converter functions for converting objects to and from maps.

name: ExtensionGenerator
desc: Generates a Dart extension for the given class name.

name: generateExtension
desc: Generates a Dart extension for the given class name.

desc: A type that helps with filtering objects from database queries.

name: Filterable

name: randomID

name: FS

name: disableCaching

name: enableNetwork

name: paginate

name: registerDeserializer
desc:
Registers a deserializer for a specific type. Needed for dynamically deserializing objects.
NOTE: This function is called by generated code in the target Flutter app.
You should not call this function directly in your code.

name: registerSerializer
desc:
Registers a serializer for a specific type. Needed for dynamically serializing objects.
NOTE: This function is called by generated code in the target Flutter app.
You should not call this function directly in your code.

name: shutdown
desc: Shuts down the Firestore instance. If used again, a new instance has to be created by calling FS.init()

desc: Configures Firestore to use the emulator instead of the real database.
